Title: Series: The Most Capital Paintings in England
Description: The Flight into Egypt; pastoral landscape with the Holy Family on a rock at right, a shepherd addressing them, his cows in foreground, ruins in left background; coat of arms of the Earl of Bute in lower margin; after Cornelis van Poelenburgh. c.1764 Etching and engraving
Curator's comments: From 'Most Capital Paintings', see biographical note on Boydell.
Associated names: Associated with: John Stuart, 3rd Earl of Bute
